body: "GH-611. pm delete removes .toon but appends a delete op to history/<id>.jsonl (file kept). Delete-on-A vs edit-on-B merge: git delete/modify resolution keeps B's .toon → deleted item silently resurrects; history left with conflict markers; validate ok:true. Fix direction: validate flags live .toon whose history ends in delete op (resurrection candidate) + conflict-marker scan in history files; document delete-vs-edit merge policy."
